@startuml Data Extraction Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

title **Data Extraction — Command Flow**\n<size:11>Via embedded Python 2.4 + Boost.Python bindings</size>

participant "Python Client\nor Godot" as Client #E3F2FD
participant "TcpServer" as TCP #E3F2FD
participant "dispatch_command\n(message_protocol)" as Proto #FFF3E0
participant "DataExtractor" as DE #FFECB3
participant "Embedded\nPython 2.4" as Py #E8EAF6
participant "CvGameCoreDLL\nBoost.Python layer" as DLL #FFEBEE

== One-Time Setup (after XML loading, before first query) ==

Proto -> DE : init_python()

DE -> Py : GetModuleHandle("python24.dll")\n+ GetProcAddress("Py_Initialize")
Py --> DE : function pointers

DE -> Py : Py_Initialize()
Py --> DE : interpreter ready

DE -> Py : GetModuleHandle("boost_python-vc71-mt-1_32.dll")\n+ GetProcAddress("init_module")
Py --> DE : init_module function

DE -> Py : boost::python::detail::init_module(\n  "CvPythonExtensions",\n  DLLPublishToPython)
Py -> DLL : DLLPublishToPython()
note right: Registers 1,331 methods:\nCyGlobalContext, CvUnitInfo,\nCvBuildingInfo, CvTechInfo,\nCvPromotionInfo, CvArtInfoUnit, ...
DLL --> Py : bindings registered
Py --> DE : module ready

...

== Query: Get All Tech Infos ==

Client -> TCP : {"cmd":"get_all_infos",\n "type":"tech"}
TCP -> Proto : dispatch
Proto -> DE : get_all_infos("tech")

DE -> Py : PyRun_SimpleString(extraction script)

Py -> DLL : gc.getNumTechInfos()
note right: CyGlobalContext::getNumTechInfos()\ncalls GC.getNumTechInfos()\n(inline, compiled with correct offsets)
DLL --> Py : 92

loop i = 0..91
  Py -> DLL : gc.getTechInfo(i)
  DLL --> Py : CvTechInfo*
  Py -> DLL : getType(), getResearchCost(), getEra()
  DLL --> Py : fields
end

Py --> DE : TSV result (temp file)

DE --> Proto : parsed JSON (via yyjson)
Proto --> TCP : {"status":"ok","data":[\n  {"type":"TECH_MYSTICISM","cost":50,"era":0},\n  {"type":"TECH_MEDITATION","cost":80,"era":0},\n  {"type":"TECH_POLYTHEISM","cost":100,"era":0},\n  ...92 total...]}
TCP --> Client : response

...

== Query: Get Specific Art Info ==

Client -> TCP : {"cmd":"get_art_info",\n "type":"unit",\n "key":"ART_DEF_UNIT_WARRIOR"}
TCP -> Proto : dispatch
Proto -> DE : get_art_info("unit", "ART_DEF_UNIT_WARRIOR")

DE -> Py : PyRun_SimpleString(lookup script)

Py -> DLL : CyArtFileMgr().getUnitArtInfo("ART_DEF_UNIT_WARRIOR")
DLL --> Py : CvArtInfoUnit*
Py -> DLL : info.getNIF()
DLL --> Py : "Art/Units/Warrior/Warrior.nif"
Py -> DLL : info.getKFM()
DLL --> Py : "Art/Units/Warrior/Warrior.kfm"
Py -> DLL : info.getScale()
DLL --> Py : 0.61

Py --> DE : TSV result

DE --> Proto : parsed JSON
Proto --> TCP : {"status":"ok","data":{\n  "type":"ART_DEF_UNIT_WARRIOR",\n  "nif":"Art/Units/Warrior/Warrior.nif",\n  "kfm":"Art/Units/Warrior/Warrior.kfm",\n  "scale":0.61}}
TCP --> Client : response

...

== Query: Single Info Lookup ==

Client -> TCP : {"cmd":"get_info",\n "type":"tech",\n "key":"TECH_MYSTICISM"}
TCP -> Proto : dispatch
Proto -> DE : get_info("tech", "TECH_MYSTICISM")

DE -> Py : PyRun_SimpleString(search script)

Py -> DLL : iterate gc.getTechInfo(i)\nuntil getType() == "TECH_MYSTICISM"
DLL --> Py : match found at index 0

Py --> DE : TSV result (single line)

DE --> Proto : parsed JSON (object, not array)
Proto --> TCP : {"status":"ok","data":{\n  "type":"TECH_MYSTICISM",\n  "cost":50,\n  "era":0}}
TCP --> Client : response

note over Client, DLL
  **Mod Compatibility:**
  The same flow works for ANY mod DLL (Rise of Mankind, Caveman2Cosmos, etc.)
  because every mod compiles its own DLLPublishToPython() with its own
  Boost.Python bindings and class layout offsets. The Python queries call
  into the loaded DLL's own compiled code — never hardcoded offsets.
end note

@enduml
